import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('Year')['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean()
    plt.plot(data_grouped.index, data_grouped.values)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the trend of Miles_per_Gallon over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
